== Customizing Git

So far, we've covered the basics of how Git works and how to use it, and we've introduced a number of
tools that help make it easier to use. In this chapter, we see how to customize Git
by introducing the hooks feature and several important configuration settings. With these, it's easy
to get Git to work exactly the way you, your company, and/or your group, want.

